BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:uBSVstDk0M5IbhL3sKKSX
SUMMARY:Family Business Exchange | Seminar: Seattle Chocolate (now Maeve)
DTSTAMP:20260410T044137Z
DTSTART:20260423T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Family Business Exchange welcomes Jean Thompson\, CEO and O
	wner of Seattle Chocolate Company\, and her daughter\, Ellie Thompson\, no
	w the second generation in the business\, for a fireside chat to share the
	ir unique journey together.  We'll hear Jean's reflections on her unexpect
	ed path into entrepreneurship and how her leadership sparked Ellie’s inter
	est in joining the company. Together\, they have navigated family-business
	 dynamics and embraced bold decisions—most notably Ellie’s leadership as D
	irector of Marketing in the recent rebranding to “Maeve.” Hear candid insi
	ghts from both perspectives on lessons learned\, strategies for fostering 
	leadership growth\, and a vision for the future that blends legacy with in
	novation—takeaways every family business leader can apply.\n\nAbout the Fa
	mily Business Exchange\n\nSeattle University’s Family Business Exchange \\
	(FBX\\) is a community of Pacific Northwest family business owners who gat
	her to engage in education\, networking\, and professional development tai
	lored specifically to their needs.\n\nFBX provides opportunities for famil
	ies to address their unique challenges through relevant programming. It se
	rves as a forum for information exchange with the goal of helping each mem
	ber thrive through future generations. Areas of best practice that we cove
	r include family business succession planning\, governance\, leadership de
	velopment and growth\, among others.\n\nAbout Equinox Business Law Group\n
	\nEquinox Business Law Group provides strategic legal counsel for entrepre
	neurs at a fixed monthly cost. Founded by Michelle Bomberger\, Equinox bri
	ngs two decades of legal expertise to entrepreneurs. As business owners th
	emselves\, they combine legal knowledge with a powerful network of industr
	y experts to support your business growth. Equinox is a proud Corporate Me
	mber of Seattle University’s Family Business Exchange.\n\nhttps://seatoday
	.6amcity.com/events/#/details/family-business-exchange-seminar-seattle-cho
	colate-now-maeve/17405352/2026-04-22T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Educ
	ation
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/family-business-exchange-
	seminar-seattle-chocolate-now-maeve/17405352/2026-04-22T00
LOCATION:Casey Building\, 530\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
